{"entityMap":{},"blocks":[{"key":"8j182","text":"Vertically Center Align Siblings","type":"header-one","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bpl79","text":"Aligning elements vertically within a container in a flexible CSS-only way can often be an annoying challenge. There are a bunch of ways to do it. Here are a few.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aduhm","text":"<table>","type":"header-two","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"vcs6vg1h","text":"HTML","type":"header-three","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"vcs958p8","text":"CSS","type":"header-three","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"vcs6a41","text":"td {\n  vertical-align: middle;\n}","type":"code-block","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b7f6l","text":"display: table;","type":"header-two","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"vcs1or1o","text":"HTML","type":"header-three","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"vcs5a1rb","text":"CSS","type":"header-three","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"vcs7el01","text":"row {\n  display: table-row;\n}\ncell {\n  display: table-cell;\n  vertical-align: middle;\n}","type":"code-block","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2b26k","text":"display: inline-block;","type":"header-two","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"vcsf5ncj","text":"HTML","type":"header-three","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"vcs46chf","text":"CSS","type":"header-three","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"vcs52mq6","text":"row {\n  white-space: nowrap;\n  display: block;\n}\ncell {\n  display: inline-block;\n  vertical-align: middle;\n  width: 33.33333%;\n  w